London & Stamford Buys $124 Million Site With Goldman Tenants

-- B y   C h r i s   S p i l l a n e
-- 
2011-04-27T07:23:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/london-stamford-buys-124-million-site-with-goldman-tenants.html
London & Stamford Property Plc (LSP) , co-
owner of the U.K.’s third-largest mall, agreed to buy One Carter Lane and Two Old Change Court from UBS Triton Property Fund for
75 million pounds ($124 million).  The site near  St. Paul’s Cathedral  in the City of London
has 125,844 square feet (11,691 square meters) of offices and
6,810 square feet of retail space, the Guernsey-based company
said today in a statement.  The buildings have an annual net income of 5.81 million
pounds, 97 percent of which comes from Goldman Sachs
International until 2018, London and Stamford said. Goldman has
a tenant break clause in March 2013.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Spillane in  London  at 
 cspillane3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
